{{see|uwe}}

==German==

===Etymology===
From Old High German [[agil]] = 'sword'. Etymological allied with Latin [[acutus]].
Indo-European root √ AK- = 'sharp'. 

===Pronunciation===
[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'uwɚ/

===Proper noun===
'''Uwe'''

# a male christian name/[[given name]] with Scandinavian / Old Frisian  [http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frisian_language] origin, "The Go-Ahead", "The Enterprising Spirt", "The Free Spirit" - from the Old Norse language [http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old-Norse] "ove": "cutting edge of a sword".

